	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.90]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Shroud of Death can be obtained from various high level mobs located in Velious, not solely PoG. <br><br>Its a lvl 55 Alteration spell that costs 100 mana, is self-only, procs 46-50 pt lifetap, has a max duration of ~20 minutes &amp; has a casting time of 3 seconds.&nbsp;&nbsp;It does not stack with the earlier lifetap procs, nor will it stack with Mental Corruption (duuhhh).  As Mental Corruption ONLY works on mobs that are casters, but Shroud of Death works on all mobs, the choice is generally clear for which buff to cast.<br><br>As stated below, I seldom go into battle without it.  Its a decent spell that is very efficient, increases your DPS &amp; also (by extension) increases your HP.<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
