	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.90]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Shroud of Death is a dropped spell, not necessarily in PoG only, but many have gotten it from there.&nbsp;&nbsp;I find it interesting that you saw it for sale by a vendor on the moon, as that is usually not the case with this spell.<br><br>If you do not have it, but are nearing 55, I would not hesitate in getting it.  I seldom go into battle without it, as its one of the most efficient lifetaps we get.<br><br>For the cost of 100 mana, you are armed with a proc that taps 46-50 HP over the duration of approx 20 min.  During the duration of the buff, it will proc a ton of times, the actual number dependent on various factors, but expecting 30-40 procs is probably not that unreasonable.  That is, by FAR, the most efficient lifetap spells, if the the most efficient one, in the game.  The problem is, you cant control when it procs.<br><br>Stacking lifetap DoTs is a lot of fun.  Vampiric embrace, Shroud of Death, Greenmist, and / or Inn Curse make for a SK having a lot more HP then just what his total is at the start of the fight.<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
