	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=631><span id=Guru>Sir Parttime</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>142 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Greetings,<br><br>Actually, the AC you get from an item is a straight calculation depending on your class.&nbsp;&nbsp;Warriors get the highest at 1.6 AC per AC of item with other classes getting less.  So your example of a 10 AC item giving you 14 AC on your shadowkight is just about right on.<br><br>The rest of it (damage avoidance and mitigation)are based on skills like defense, dodge, perry and to some extent agility.  I have heard, but do not quote me, that agility is really not that important.  However, again that is only what I have heard.<br><br>The only time I know race has anything to do with AC is when you are an Iksar.  Iksar get a racial AC bonus capped at 50 AC at 60th level if the rumors are true.  (One of the big benefits of at 20% experience penalty I guess)<br><br>Hope this help and good hunting.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></td></tr>
