	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Innoruuk's Curse is the Shadowknight epic weapon.&nbsp;&nbsp;Its a 40/45 2HS that has the following stats:<br><br>20str, 15dex, 15int, svmagic15, svfire15, svcold15, svpoison5, svdisease5, hp60, mana40.  It also procs Soul Consumption, which is perhaps its greatest attribute, a 250 lifetap DoT over 5 ticks (30 seconds).<br><br>Some may argue, however, that the SK has 2 epic weapons.  What originally started out as IKS SK only, probably due to the terrible faction associated with IKS, which makes doing Inn Curse VERY hard to do, has been expanded to all classes. After upgrading your initial weapon like 9 times (all via quests), you can receive:<br><br>Greenmist, 18/22 1HS, ac5, str5, dex5, int10, svmagic25, svpoison5, svdisease10 &amp; it procs Greenmist.  Greenmist proc is a 120 Lifetap DoT over a WHOPPING 8 ticks (48 seconds), a str tap of 20, &amp; a ac tap of 9.<br><br>Personally, I like Inn Curse far more than Greenmist &amp; I would think it silly that any class, except for a IKS, would even go through all the hassle of getting Greenmist, as the reward doesnt seem to equal the work required to get it.  Also, 18/22 is good, but definitely NOT great &amp; the proc also seem to leave a little more to be desired....<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
