VER, Inn Curse is STILL MORE DAMAGING.  YES, even against Shissar.  What people fail to realize is how killer that proc is:  250 HP Lifetap over 30 seconds is KILLER.  That is about 8.33 more DPS once it goes off.  Also, by the time you get either of these weapons, your DEX is high enough to make them proc on a fairly regularily basis &amp; I can tell you from experience that it procs fairly regularily.<br><br>Believe me, I think that is terrible &amp; so WISH that Verant would make the lifetap proc on Greenmist A LITTLE BETTER.  As it stands, it leaves something to be desired.  Also, 18/22 is NOT that great by any stretch for an SK.  It should probably be something like 20/22 to make it more respectible.<br><br>Inn Curse is not only far more consistent a weapon than Greenmist (works great against all mobs, not only against Shissar), but its more damaging most of the time.<br><br>Therefore, to say that you are in a guild that requires you to use that weapon ONLY really makes sense if you are the MT.  Why?  You will have a ton more AC, because you can wield a shield with it, get the proc of 9 ac, and also the 5 ac from Greenmist.  Because is has little, IF ANYTHING, to do with damage output.  Greenmist loses most of the time.<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
