	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102572116852940>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=102572116852940>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102572116852940>DPS</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102572116852940#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 3rd 2:43 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I know Im asking for trouble with this post, but I had a LONG discussion with a MNK in our guild last night about damage per second (&quot;DPS&quot;), duel wield &amp; delay, both hasted &amp; not hasted &amp; I felt it necessary to let people know the correct formulas so they can make their own conclusion.&nbsp;&nbsp; This post will focus on DPS aspect mostly.  I can discuss the other things in a different post if needed.<br><br>The numbers for DPS are all mathematically calculated.  There is no bias anywhere &amp; they are what they are.  However, the MNK just wanted to believe what he wanted to believe, as it is believed in mainstream play &amp;, therefore, MUST BE CORRECT.  Nothing could be further from the truth.(NOTE:  I am ONLY referring to dly/dmg; I am NOT factoring in stats, procs, etc. those of which are NOT easily quantifiable, nor measurable)<br><br>The whole converation began when, in guild chat, a member asked what weapon would be better in his OFFHAND; lammy or LSoEE.  For those of you who arent familiar with these weapons, both are 1HS, with lammy being 19dly, 9dmg, and LSoEE being 29dly, 16dmg. The formula for simple DPS is as follows:<br><br>DPS = (dmg*2+1) / (dly/10)<br><br>With the little work of a calculator, it becomes clear REALLY QUICK that LSoEE is FAR SUPERIOR to lammy in the offhand, at ANY LEVEL (lammy is NOT a good weapon at ALL; i know NOT why it is so popular).  Why is it imporatnt for me to say at ANY LEVEL?  Well, the offhand does NOT get the damage bonus that is applied when wielding a weapon in the primary hand.  Hence, in the offhand, you put YOUR BEST RATIO to get maximum damage.<br><br>In your PRIMARY hand, however, the formula becomes slightly more complex, as you now have to figure in a dmg bonus.  Again, just using a calculator, you will discover that once a character passes 49, the lammy will do more damage.  The overall weapon performance can be evaluated with the following formula:<br><br>Weapon performance = (2*weapon dmg+1+dmg bonus) / dly.<br><br>Therefore, SPD (or dly) becomes important for the primary hand, as the more hits equates to teh dmg bonus getting applied more &amp; more.  That is why at lower levels the LSoEE was doign more damage, but once a certain level was reached &amp; the damage bonus increased, the lammy passed it up.  Therefore, ratio AND speed for the primary hand is needed to max damage.  The only way to really know for the primary hand, however, is to run the numbers.<br><br>Here's an interesting fact to stump the WAR friends with.  When you start playing around with these formulas, you will quickly discover that lammy is a TERRIBLE weapon &amp; an awful purchase.  They generally sell for 3kish on my server &amp; WURM sells for about 1.5k.  Wurm is a MUCH better weapon in primary hand until 58 &amp; you can get it at a far cheaper price.  As far as the offhand, same thing.  Lammy costs far more than Centi LS or SS, yet those have better ratios &amp; will do more damage.  Tell that to most WAR &amp; they will immediately say, &quot;NO WAY!!  This is so much faster!!&quot;  Im like--no @#%^--but the damage of 9 IS AWFUL!!!  Why cant people face the facts sometimes???<br><br>Often, taunt will be cited as a reason for a spd weapon, which i dont buy for one second.  The absolute BEST taunting weapon that I have seen to date has got to be Neraldi's Lance, which is a molasses slow, 45 dly, 2HP weapon.  It does, however, have 44 dmg, so perhaps its overall damage that generates the most taunt???  Hmm<br><br>The reason that this applies to us SKs is that we still have to go through the same calculations, but we only have our primary hand to calculate. I urge you all to use the formula(s) above &amp; wield the weapon that generates the highest number.  Your efforts will be rewarded &amp; you will be armed with a far greater weapon DPS understanding than most of the players out there.<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
