	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153688><span id=Scholar>colinmarsh</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>61 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>lunatic,<br><br>i won't profess to fully understand all the calcuations but i think your calculation does not consider double attack.<br><br>the lower a delay of a weapon the more chances it has to double attack in a given time span. this same principle would apply i think when considering both dual wielding and critical hits i think.<br><br>critical hits is a direct parallel i would think. the more often you swing, the better chance of crit. hit (unless dmg. has something to do with crit. hit. i really don't know for sure i've never played a warrior so i'm kind of talking out of my ... well you know).<br><br>with dual wield i thought that you only swing with the 2nd weapon if you hit with the first. so i guess that would mean again. more swings, more chance to deal extra dmg. by swinging 2nd weapon. speed would definately help there.<br><br>regardless of whether or not i have the crit. hit and dual wield thing right, your formula definately doesn't mention double attack so i don't think it tells the whole story.<br><br>to me you need to have an idea of how often you double attack vs. not double attacking. i know there is a formula for this but i don't know it. with it however, one could combine the ratio calculation you supplied with chance of double attack and come up with an idea of which is better.<br><br>i'm very curious about this i think i could figure a really good ratio that does take into account double attack if i had the following information.<br><br>1. what does delay mean exactly. does a delay of 19 mean you hit once per 1.9 seconds, or something else? i really have NO idea.<br><br>2. how do you calculate your chance to double hit. prolly based on offense + weapon skill divided by something or other. maybe dex figures in???<br><br>regardless we could set constants like say lvl 40 with dex of 80 and we could come up with fair comparisons.<br><br>if anyone has this info i'd love you to post it.<br><br>lastly. your post is very timely since i am debating buying a centi ls to replace my sporali defender blade.<br><br>17/37 vs 14/27. your formula definately helps out there since the DPS of centi is 1.07 vs the sporali's .95 . that combined with the fact that i will swing the centi more for double attack having a lower delay means the decision is a no-brainer. centi it is.. ;)<br><br>/auction WTS sporali defender blade - *chuckle*</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
