	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=102573885854296>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102573885854296>RE: DPS</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102573885854296#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 3rd 7:38 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.30]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Haha.&nbsp;&nbsp;Reasoned yourself out of it?  =)<br><br>Actually, I think that you are correct in your 2nd post.  Double attack shouldnt play a role.  For instance, let's assume that Wurm had a DPS of 12 &amp; lammy had a DPS of 10, and your character had a 50% chance to double attack.  To determine which weapon would be better, you would increase the DPS of both weapons by 50%.  As such, you would adjust the DPS numbers as follows:<br><br>Wurm = 12 + (12*50%) = 18<br><br>Lammy = 10 + (10*50%) = 16<br><br>In this example, Wurm is still better when factoring in double attack.<br><br>Since you asked, the formula to calculate the percentage to double attack is as follows:<br><br>(Skill + Level) / 500.<br><br>The result should then be converted into a percentage.  As such, a lvl 50 character with 200 double attack skill has a 50% chance to double attack.<br><br>Re: Critical hits, see logic above.<br><br>Re: Duel wielding;  No, it is NOT true that a faster delay weapon gives duel wield a better chance to succeed.  You can put a lantern in your primary hand &amp; still get substantially the same results out of your offhand.  The formula, for those interested, to duel wield is as follows:<br><br>(Skill + Level) / 600 &amp; convert to a percentage, similar to double attack.  As such, a lvl 50 character, with a skill of 200 Duel wield, has a 41.67% chance to duel wield with the offhand.<br><br>It has nothing to do at all with what you are wielding in your primary hand.<br><br>As far as I know, delay is a measurement of time, stated in terms of seconds times 10.  So, in your example, yes, dly of 19 would be 1.9 secs.<br><br>Hope this helps  =P<br><br>Lunatic<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
