	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=631><span id=Guru>Sir Parttime</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>142 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Believe it or not you get to add both the range of the bow and the arrow to get range.&nbsp;&nbsp;So, a bow with range of 150 and an arrow with range of 125 means that you get a total range of 275.  <br><br>This is one of the main reasons why bow are not necessarily a bad weapon for a Shadow Knight.  When pulling a bow may give you a lot of distance in comparison to a spell.<br><br>Good Hunting...</p>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></td></tr>
