	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Substantially all the time I would heavily recommend the STA gear over just about all else.&nbsp;&nbsp;Only in a few situations would I recommend against it, as higher STA leads to higher HP, which helps at tanking.  <br><br>However, soloing is one of those times where I would choose the INT gear &amp; increase your mana pool over STA as, if you can land it right, you wont be getting hit much at all &amp; you primarily want to increase your DPS as much as you can--even at the sacrafice of AC.  Granted, if/when fear wears off &amp; the mob is hitting you, you will quickly wish that you had the STA &amp; AC back, but I am assuming that the reverse-kiting will go reasonably well.<br><br>I recommend to be careful though.  Reverse-kiting with clinging darkness is not exactly a piece of cake, as the snare is not exactly the greatest...<br><br>You will enjoy reverse-kiting a lot more when you get engulfing darkness.<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
