	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I think we are splitting hairs...&nbsp;&nbsp;=)<br><br>AC important when fear-kiting?  Perhaps if the MOB is on ya, but he's probably gonna be snared anyways, so if you can't get the fear spell off, just run a little from him &amp; pop it again (note that you NOT have to be looking directly at the MOB&amp;#8212;all that is required is that he is in your line of sight from where your character stands; I frequently use this strategy for pulling).  Again though, I think we're splitting hairs and you could go either way &amp; be fine.<br><br>As far as CLR &amp; fear-kiting, certainly ANY class is going to be able to help defeat a MOB.  Too many people seem to miss that fact.  I will group with anyone--class matters not &amp; I do not discriminate (unlike many Im sad to say).  However, I would rather have just about any other class over a CLR when fear-kiting.  I believe that most all of the others classes can contribute to fear-kiting more than a CLR can, but perhaps that is just me.<br><br>As far as tanking SKs, I agree--ANY SK can tank.  one of the absolute scariest SKs I have seen is an ERU SK!!  Granted, he's in full Kael armor (of course lvl 60) &amp; has just about all of his tanking AA abilities but we'll overlook that point (haha).  I suppose, however, that I just HAVE TO BELIEVE that MORE POINTS, both core stats &amp; HP, IS SUPERIOR TO FEWER POINTS.  How can it not be??  Further, it is VERY HARD to argue that INT is superior to STR/STA/AGI/DEX for an SK and it is NOT easily quantifiable.<br><br>Re:  STA &amp; core stats:  The main concern I have over putting points in INT at inception is that I believe that items which give large amounts of direct mana are more efficient at later levels.  All races, save for TRL/ORG, have plenty of INT at inception to not have to worry about putting any points into it.  If you are a casual gamer, and were playing an ORG/TRL SK, I DEFINITELY would NOT recommend putting all points into STA at inception.  However, if you are a hard-core gamer &amp; believe that you will hit 60, sure, Id dump all my points into STA, even as an ORG/TRL, because the INT/mana producing items you will get will generally overcome any stupidity that you have an inception   =P.  Also, a high INT will (substantially) only give you a larger mana pool; it doesnt help with mana regen.  Hence, you will, theoretically, have longer down time getting your mana back. Granted, I would rather have the larger mana pool, as its safer, but it really isnt that big a deal.<br><br>Also, make no mistake about it, I think that discussing a topic like this is very good &amp; I do NOT see this as annoying.  For, as stated in Dead Poets Society, &amp;#8220;as soon as you think you understand something, you must look at it from a different point of view.&amp;#8221;  I believe that these threads do that, so I hope that people enjoy reading them.<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
