	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=102450768869002>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102450768869002>RE: Clinging Darkness & Engulfing Darkness</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102450768869002#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jun 19th 1:37 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Sure you can cast both clinging darkness &amp; engulfing darkness on a mob, but they will not stack--I think that engulfing will overwrite clinging.<br><br>On a marginally unrelated note, engulfing is a good snare for when you are in a group.&nbsp;&nbsp;I use it now even in SEB, Velks, etc due to the quicker casting time over dooming (4 secs vs. 2.45 secs).  If I am acting as the snarer of my group, I mem engulfing every time.  Knock on wood, I haven&amp;#8217;t had a problem yet with engulfing.<br><br>Dooming, however, is DEFENITELY the way to go when fear-kiting.  Dooming makes fear-kiting about 1000x easier because there is quite a noticeable difference between the run rate of the mob when dooming is on him (dooming is 20% better, from 40% reduction in run rate for engulfing to 60% with dooming) and it lasts twice as long (assuming no break in the snare, 2 min for engulfing vs. 4 min for dooming).  The MOB practically crawls to you (and then away when you fear him).<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>Lunatic<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
